#: ../../glossary.rst:29
msgid ""
"Abstract base classes complement :term:`duck-typing` by providing a way to "
"define interfaces when other techniques like :func:`hasattr` would be clumsy "
"or subtly wrong (for example with :ref:`magic methods <special-lookup>`).  "
"ABCs introduce virtual subclasses, which are classes that don't inherit from "
"a class but are still recognized by :func:`isinstance` and :func:"
"`issubclass`; see the :mod:`abc` module documentation.  Python comes with "
"many built-in ABCs for data structures (in the :mod:`collections.abc` "
"module), numbers (in the :mod:`numbers` module), streams (in the :mod:`io` "
"module), import finders and loaders (in the :mod:`importlib.abc` module).  "
"You can create your own ABCs with the :mod:`abc` module."
msgstr ""
"Classes bases abstratas (ABCs, do inglûˆs *abstract base class*) complementam "
"a :term:`tipagem pato`, fornecendo uma maneira de definir interfaces quando "
"outras tûˋcnicas, como :func:`hasattr`, seriam desajeitadas ou sutilmente "
"erradas (por exemplo, com :ref:`mûˋtodos mûÀgicos <special-lookup>`). ABCs "
"introduzem subclasses virtuais, classes que nûÈo herdam de uma classe mas "
"ainda sûÈo reconhecidas por :func:`isinstance` e :func:`issubclass`; veja a "
"documentaûÏûÈo do mû°dulo :mod:`abc`. Python vem com muitas ABCs embutidas para "
"estruturas de dados (no mû°dulo :mod:`collections.abc`), nû¤meros (no mû°dulo :"
"mod:`numbers`), fluxos (no mû°dulo :mod:`io`), localizadores e carregadores "
"de importaûÏûÈo (no mû°dulo :mod:`importlib.abc`). Vocûˆ pode criar suas "
"prû°prias ABCs com o mû°dulo :mod:`abc`."

